Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 python3,
 python3-pip,
 at-spi2-core,
 libatspi2.0-0,
gir1.2-atspi-2.0,
 libwayland-client0,
 libwayland-cursor0,
 xdg-desktop-portal-wlr,
 wlrb,
 python3-yaml,
 python3-typing-extensions
Description: DuckBotOS computer-use — desktop automation MCP server
 Installs computer-use-linux as a systemd-per-user MCP server for
 automated desktop interaction and accessibility-driven control.
 .
 AT-SPI2 accessibility bus integration for reading UI elements.
 Wayland portal for screen capture and input events.
 MCP protocol server exposing desktop automation to Hermes/OpenClaw.
 .
 Per-user systemd service: computer-use@username.service
 Config: ~/.config/computer-use-linux.yaml
 Socket: ~/.computer-use/computer-use.sock (user-owned Unix socket)
 MCP:    http://127.0.0.1:18765/mcp (localhost only)
 .
 Requires Wayland session (Weston kiosk in DuckBotOS).
 Not compatible with X11-only sessions.
 Requires active user session with accessibility bus running.
